entity_a.description: Nanoacademic Technologies Inc. is a Canadian company established in Montreal, specializing in the development and licensing of advanced atomistic simulation and quantum modeling software. Their tools, including QTCAD®, NanoDCAL, and RESCU, are used globally by universities, government labs, and private companies to predict properties and performance of next-generation materials and quantum devices, aiming to reduce R&D costs and accelerate innovation.

entity_b.description: Hongzhiwei Technology, based in Shanghai, China, is a developer of material design and process simulation software and cloud platforms. The company provides solutions for material design, process simulation, high-performance computing cloud platforms, and customized calculation solutions, with applications in semiconductor materials and device design, electronic materials, battery materials, chemical materials, and alloy materials design. They collaborate with universities and research institutes.
